# UDS Design System

You are building UI with the **Urban Design System (UDS)**. Always use UDS tokens and components. Never hardcode colors, spacing, fonts, or reinvent components that UDS provides. For custom layouts that UDS doesn't cover, still use UDS tokens for ALL values.

**Docs:** https://sbajwa32.github.io/uds-docs/
**AI context (JSON):** https://sbajwa32.github.io/uds-docs/ai-context.json
**Install:** `npm install uds-core` then `import 'uds-core/uds.css'`
**Icons:** Material Symbols Outlined — browse at https://fonts.google.com/icons

## Framework Detection

Check `package.json` to determine the framework:
- If `react` in dependencies → React patterns (className, hooks, NO uds.js)
- If `vue` in dependencies → Vue patterns (class, ref, script setup, NO uds.js)
- Otherwise → vanilla HTML (class, uds.js handles behavior)

## Required External Links

ALWAYS include in `<head>`:
```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;700&family=Poppins:wght@400;500;700&family=Roboto:wght@400;500;700&family=Lexend:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined:opsz,wght,FILL,GRAD@20..48,100..700,0..1,-50..200" rel="stylesheet" />
```

## Token Architecture — Primitives vs Semantics

UDS has TWO layers of CSS custom properties:

**PRIMITIVE tokens** (`--uds-primitive-*`):
Raw palette values. Example: `--uds-primitive-color-blue-60-M: #005ff0`
These are the raw building blocks. They NEVER change across themes.
**NEVER use primitives in component code.**

**SEMANTIC tokens** (`--uds-color-*`, `--uds-space-*`, `--uds-font-*`, etc.):
Purpose-based tokens that reference primitives via `var()` chains.
Example: `--uds-color-text-interactive: var(--uds-primitive-color-blue-60-M)`
These CHANGE values when themes/modes switch.
**ALWAYS use semantic tokens.**

The flow: `Figma variable → Primitive CSS token → Semantic CSS token → Your code`

**RULE: If a variable name contains `primitive`, NEVER use it. Only use semantic tokens.**

## Theming — How It Works

UDS supports 6 color modes, 4 font families, 3 font scales, and 2 density modes. Theming works by setting data attributes on `<html>`. When these change, semantic token VALUES change automatically — your code stays the same.

**Example — same CSS, different themes:**
```
--uds-color-surface-main:  #fafafa   ← light mode (default)
--uds-color-surface-main:  #1a1a1a   ← when data-color-scheme="dark"
--uds-color-text-interactive: #005ff0 ← base brand (default)
--uds-color-text-interactive: #0066cc ← when data-theme="resman"
```

Your component uses `var(--uds-color-surface-main)` and it works in ALL themes.

**WHY primitives break theming:**
`--uds-primitive-color-blue-60-M` is ALWAYS `#005ff0` regardless of theme.
`--uds-color-text-interactive` changes per brand/mode. Use the semantic one.

**Available modes** (set on `<html>`):
| Attribute | Values | Default |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| `data-color-scheme` | `dark` | light |
| `data-theme` | `resman`, `anyonehome`, `inhabit` | base |
| `data-font` | `poppins`, `roboto`, `lexend` | Inter |
| `data-font-scale` | `smaller`, `larger` | default |
| `data-density` | `comfortable` | default (compact) |

**To implement dark mode** — just set `<html data-color-scheme="dark">`. All tokens adapt. No code changes.
**To implement brand switching** — set `<html data-theme="resman">`. Accent colors shift. Components unchanged.

## Tokens — When to Use Which

### Surface Colors (backgrounds)
| Token | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| `--uds-color-surface-page-main` | Full page background |
| `--uds-color-surface-main` | Card / content area backgrounds |
| `--uds-color-surface-subtle` | Headers, table headers, secondary areas |
| `--uds-color-surface-alt` | Zebra stripes, alternate rows, code blocks |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-default` | Primary button fill, active accent |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-hover` | Hover state of interactive-default |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-subtle` | Focused backgrounds, soft selection |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-subtle-hover` | Hover on subtle interactive |
| `--uds-color-surface-interactive-none` | Transparent interactive (ghost) |
| `--uds-color-surface-info` / `success` / `warning` / `error` | Status-colored filled containers |
| `--uds-color-surface-info-subtle` / `success-subtle` / etc. | Light-tinted status containers |

### Text Colors
| Token | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| `--uds-color-text-primary` | Main body text, headings |
| `--uds-color-text-secondary` | Helper text, labels, captions, timestamps |
| `--uds-color-text-inverse` | Text on dark/filled backgrounds (buttons, prominent badges) |
| `--uds-color-text-interactive` | Links, active tab labels, selected items |
| `--uds-color-text-disabled` | Disabled form fields, inactive items |
| `--uds-color-text-info` / `success` / `warning` / `error` | Status messages, validation text |

### Border Colors
| Token | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| `--uds-color-border-primary` | Default borders (input fields, cards) |
| `--uds-color-border-secondary` | Subtle dividers, table cell borders |
| `--uds-color-border-interactive` | Selected/active borders, focus accents |
| `--uds-color-border-error` | Error state borders |
| `--uds-color-border-outline-focus-visible` | Focus rings (keyboard navigation) |

